ficant probability of deexcitation to form ground-state molecules bound by\nup to 1500 cm-1. Our analysis of the role of spin-orbit coupling concerns the\ncharacter of the mixed states in general and is important for both\nphotoassociation and stimulated Raman deexcitation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 31 Oct 2008 15:02:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 30 Jan 2009 08:19:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-06-16"}
